         <abstract>
            <p>In this paper a new approach is developed for analyzing the discontinuous Galerkin method for hyperbolic equations. For a model problem in $R^2$, the method is shown to converge at a rate $O(h^{n + 1})$ when applied with $n$th degree polynomial approximations over a semiuniform triangulation, assuming sufficient regularity in the solution.</p>
          </abstract>
